5 The вАШ<insert>вАЩ key
********************

The вАШ<insert>вАЩ key is a prefix for other keys:
   вАҐ for drawing arrows, squares, crosses, o-shapes glyphs,
   вАҐ for handling rectangles,
   вАҐ for inserting вАШ# = - +вАЩ which otherwise change the brush style,
   вАҐ for trying a choice of mono-spaced fonts.

   Why вАШ<insert>вАЩ?  Because:
   вАҐ вАШUnilineвАЩ tries to leave their original meaning to as many keys as
     possible,
   вАҐ the standard meaning of вАШ<insert>вАЩ is to toggle the
     вАШoverwrite-modeвАЩ; but вАШUnilineвАЩ is already in вАШoverwrite-modeвАЩ, and
     de-activating overwrite would break вАШUnilineвАЩ.

   So preempting вАШ<insert>вАЩ does not sacrifice anything.

   *Customization*

   Another key may be defined instead of вАШ<insert>вАЩ.  Type:

     M-x customize-variable uniline-key-insert


