7.3 Moving a rectangular region
===============================

Select a region, then press вАШ<insert>вАЩ.

   Use arrow keys to move the rectangle around.  A numeric prefix may be
used to move the rectangle that many characters.
   вАҐ Under вАШHydraвАЩ, be sure to specify the numeric prefix with just
     digits, without the вАШAltвАЩ key.  Typing вАШ15 <left>вАЩ moves the
     rectangle 15 characters to the left.  вАШM-15 <left>вАЩ does not work.
   вАҐ Under вАШTransientвАЩ, use the вАШAltвАЩ key, like anywhere else in
     вАШEmacsвАЩ.  Type вАШM-15 <left>вАЩ to move the selected rectangle 15
     characters to the left.

   Press вАШqвАЩ, вАШ<return>вАЩ, or вАШC-gвАЩ to stop moving the rectangle.

   The вАШC-_вАЩ key may also be used to undo the previous movements, even
though the selection is still active.



