8.1 Tracing a contour
=====================



       вХ≠вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХЃ
     вХ≠вФАвХѓA.written.textвХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХЃ
     вФВoutlined by the.`contour'вФВ
     вХ∞вФАвХЃfunction.getsвХґвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ
       вХ∞вХЃa.surroundingвХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХЃ
        вХ∞вФАвХЃline.in.the.currentвФВ
          вХ∞вФАвХЃbrush.styleвХ≠вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ
            вХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ

   Choose or change the brush style with any of вАШ-,+,=_,#,<delete>вАЩ.
Put the cursor anywhere on the shape or outside but touching it.  Then
type:

   вАШ<insert> cвАЩ

   A contour line is traced (or erased if brush style is вАШ<delete>вАЩ)
around the contiguous shape close to the cursor.

   When hitting capital letter: вАШ<insert> S-CвАЩ the contour is
overwritten.  This means that if there was already a different style of
line on the contour path, it is overwritten.

   The shape is distinguished because it floats in a blank characters
ocean.  For the shake of the contour function, blank characters are
those containing lines as drawn by вАШUnilineвАЩ (including true blank
characters).  Locations outside the buffer are also considered blank.

   The algorithm has an upper limit of вАШ10000вАЩ steps.  This avoids an
infinite loop in which the algorithm may end up in some rare cases.  One
of those cases is when the contour crosses a new-page character,
displayed by вАШEmacsвАЩ as вАШ^LвАЩ.  вАШ10000вАЩ steps require a fraction of a
second to run.  For shapes really huge, you may launch the contour
command once again, at the point where the previous run ended.

   This вАШ10000вАЩ steps limit is customizable.  Type:

     M-x customize-variable uniline-contour-max-steps


