8.2 Flood-fill
==============




     this.text.surrounds      this.text.surrounds
     .                 /      .вЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТ/
     .                //вХґвФАвФАвФАвЦЈвХі.вЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТ//
     ...            ////      ...вЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТвЦТ////
       ...a.hole/////           ...a.hole/////


   A hollow shape is a contiguous region of identical characters (not
necessarily blank), surrounded by a boundary of different characters.
The end of the buffer in any direction is also considered a boundary.

   Put the cursor anywhere in the hole.  Then type:

   вАШ<insert> iвАЩ

   Answer by giving a character to fill the hole.

   If instead of a character, вАШSPCвАЩ or вАШDELвАЩ is typed, then a shade of
grey character is picked.  вАШSPCвАЩ selects a darker grey than the one the
point is on, while вАШDELвАЩ selects a lighter.  There are 5 shades of grey
in the UNICODE standard: вАШ" вЦСвЦТвЦУвЦИ"вАЩ.  Those grey characters are well
supported by the suggested fonts.

   вАШC-yвАЩ is also an option.  The first character in the top of the kill
ring will be chosen as the filling character.  (The kill ring is filled
by functions like вАШC-kвАЩ or вАШM-wвАЩ, unrelated to вАШUnilineвАЩ).

   Typing вАШ<return>вАЩ or вАШC-gвАЩ aborts the filling operation.

   A rectangular shape may also be filled.
   вАҐ Mark a region
   вАҐ вАШ<insert> iвАЩ
   вАҐ answer which character should be used to fill.

   There is no limit on the area to fill.  Therefore, the filling
operation may flood the entire buffer (but no more).


