11.1 Selecting Hydra or Transient
=================================

Two files are compiled when installing вАШUnilineвАЩ
   вАҐ вАШuniline-hydra.elвАЩ
   вАҐ вАШuniline-transient.elвАЩ

   One of them should be loaded (but not both).  There are several ways.
The cleanest is вАШuse-packageвАЩ.  Add those lines to your вАШ~/.emacsвАЩ file:

     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   or:

     (use-package uniline-transient
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   The following key sequences can assist in modifying the вАШ.emacsвАЩ
file:
   вАҐ вАШ<INS> * HвАЩ
   вАҐ вАШ<INS> * TвАЩ

   Note: there used to be a customizable setting to switch between the
two interfaces.  This had many issues.  One of them is that the
native-compiler is blind to all user-customized settings.

   There is a third file, вАШuniline-code.elcвАЩ.  Loading
вАШuniline-hydra.elcвАЩ or вАШuniline-transient.elcвАЩ automatically loads
вАШuniline-core.elcвАЩ.


File: uniline.info,  Node: Instantly selecting Hydra or Transient,  Next: One-liner menus,  Prev: Selecting Hydra or Transient,  Up: Hydra or Transient?

11.2 Instantly selecting Hydra or Transient
===========================================

It is now possible to switch user interfaces on the fly.

   To do so, look at the "Customize" entry in the Uniline menu.  This
menu is available:
   вАҐ from the menu-bar at the top of the Emacs screen (if not made
     invisible),
   вАҐ by left-clicking on вАШ"Uniline"вАЩ in the mode-line, at the bottom of
     the Emacs screen.

   Note that the changes are for the current session only.  To
permanently choose Hydra or Transient, change your
=~/.emacs=initialization file as describe in *note Selecting Hydra or
Transient::.

   The actions performed by the menu are:
   вАҐ вАШ(load-library "uniline-hydra")вАЩ
   вАҐ вАШ(load-library "uniline-transient")вАЩ

   You can execute them directly or by other means.


File: uniline.info,  Node: One-liner menus,  Next: The Hydra interface,  Prev: Instantly selecting Hydra or Transient,  Up: Hydra or Transient?

11.3 One-liner menus
====================

The multi-lines menus in Hydra and Transient are quite useful for casual
users.  For seasoned users, those huge textual menus may distract them
from their workflow.

   It is now possible to switch to less distracting textual menus.  They
are displayed in the echo-area on a single line.

   To do so, type:
   вАҐ вАШC-tвАЩ within a sub-mode (glyph insertion mode, rectangle handling,
     etc.)
   вАҐ вАШC-h TABвАЩ at the top-level.

   This will flip between the two sizes of textual menus.  It also
affects the welcome message, the one displayed when entering the
вАШUnilineвАЩ minor mode.

   The current size is controlled by the вАШuniline-hint-styleвАЩ variable:
   вАҐ вАШtвАЩ for full fledged messages over several lines
   вАҐ вАШ1вАЩ for one-liner messages
   вАҐ вАШ0вАЩ for no message at all

   The variable is "buffer-local", which means that it can take distinct
values on distinct buffers.

   Its default value can be customized and saved for future sessions:

   вАШM-x customize-variable uniline-hint-styleвАЩ

   After customization it can be changed later, on a buffer per buffer
basis, with the вАШC-tвАЩ or вАШC-h TABвАЩ keys.

   Transient natively offers a similar setting: вАШtransient-show-popupвАЩ.
(There is no such variable in Hydra).  It can be customized with вАШtвАЩ,
вАШnilвАЩ, вАШ0вАЩ (zero), or a number.  This is similar but not exactly the
same as the Hydra behavior and the вАШuniline-hint-styleвАЩ.  the Transient
setting stays in effect until the вАШC-tвАЩ or вАШC-h TABвАЩ keys are not used,
.  As soon as one of those keys is invoked, вАШtransient-show-popupвАЩ is
toggled (which does not happens in Transient alone).  The change is kept
in effect throughout the вАШUnilineвАЩ session, but no longer.


