12.2 Insert key
===============

By default, the вАШ<insert>вАЩ or вАШINSвАЩ key is the prefix for most of the
вАШUnilineвАЩ actions.  Some computers do not have an вАШINSвАЩ key, or it is
bound to some other command (Apple?).

   This can be changed temporarily or permanently.  The customization
allows to set several keys at the same time.

   Depending on whether вАШEmacsвАЩ is run in a graphical environment or a
text-only terminal, either the вАШ<insert>вАЩ or the вАШ<insertchar>вАЩ events
are generated by the вАШINSвАЩ key.  Therefore, by default вАШUnilineвАЩ defines
both events as the вАШINSвАЩ key.

   Variable вАШuniline-key-insertвАЩ.


