13.1 Language environment
=========================

The so called "language environment" in Emacs can cause unwanted line
breaks, like in this drawing:




     вХґвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХЃ
                            вФВ           вФВ
                            вФВ           вФВ
                            вФВ           вФВ
                            вХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ
        unexpected broken lines

     вХґвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХЃ
           вФВ           вФВ
           вФВ           вФВ
           вФВ           вФВ
           вХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ
        expected continuous lines


   The above example was drawn first with the вАШChinese-BIG5вАЩ language
environment, then with the вАШEnglishвАЩ environment.

   There is nothing specific about вАШChinese-BIG5вАЩ.  It is just an
instance picked out from more than 100 language environments.

     C-x RET l Chinese-BIG5
     C-x RET l English

   In вАШChinese-BIG5вАЩ, some characters are considered twice as wide as
standard characters.  Whereas in вАШEnglishвАЩ, all characters needed by
Uniline are 1 unit wide.

   Thanks to *rumengling* (GitHub) for discovering and diagnosing the
issue!

   To workaround the issue, when entering вАШuniline-modeвАЩ, the width of
all characters Uniline uses is checked.  If some of them are more than
1, the вАШchar-width-tableвАЩ variable is patched.

   What are the consequences of this patch?  The вАШchar-width-tableвАЩ
variable is an Emacs global.  Therefore the patch by Uniline will affect
all buffers.  As the characters touched by the patch are graphic, and
have nothing to do with Chinese, it should not have any significance on
text written in Chinese.

   It was pondered whether Uniline should put back вАШchar-width-tableвАЩ at
its original value upon exiting вАШuniline-modeвАЩ, or leaving the patch.
For now, it has been decided to leave it.  Because anyway, intertwining
several вАШuniline-modeвАЩ and changes to the language environment is
intractable.

   In case of something, re-setting the language environment to its same
value cancels the patch to вАШchar-width-tableвАЩ by Uniline.


