13.2 Mouse support
==================

The out-of-the-box mouse support of вАШEmacsвАЩ works perfectly.  Except
when the mouse clicks on a position outside the buffer.  This happens
when clicking past the end of a too short line, or past the end of the
buffer.

   To handle those cases, a few standard вАШEmacsвАЩ functions have been
extended to add blank characters or blank lines.  Doing so, the
mouse-click now falls on a valid part of the buffer.  Of course, those
extensions are only active on вАШuniline-modeвАЩ activated buffers.

   Beware that when the window is at the same time zoomed with вАШC-x C-+
C--вАЩ AND horizontally scrolled with вАШC-x <вАЩ, the cursor positioning is
not accurate.  This is due to вАШEmacsвАЩ limitations and bugs.  Just click
twice to fix the inaccuracy.


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Picture-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Prev: Mouse support,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.3 Compatibility with Picture-mode
====================================

вАШPicture-modeвАЩ and вАШuniline-modeвАЩ are compatible.  Their features
overlap somehow:
   вАҐ Both implement an unlimited buffer in east and south directions.
   вАҐ Both visually truncate long lines (actual text is not truncated).
   вАҐ Both set the overwrite mode (вАШuniline-modeвАЩ activates
     вАШoverwrite-modeвАЩ, while вАШpicture-modeвАЩ re-implements it)
   вАҐ Both are able to draw rectangles (вАШuniline-modeвАЩ in UNICODE,
     вАШpicture-modeвАЩ in ASCII), copy and yank them.

   They also have features unique to each:
   вАҐ вАШPicture-modeвАЩ writes in 8 possible directions
   вАҐ вАШPicture-modeвАЩ handles TAB stops
   вАҐ вАШUniline-modeвАЩ draws lines and arrows


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Prev: Compatibility with Picture-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.4 Compatibility with Artist-mode
===================================

вАШArtist-modeвАЩ and вАШuniline-modeвАЩ are mostly incompatible.  This is
because вАШartist-modeвАЩ preempts the arrow keys, which give access to a
large part of вАШuniline-modeвАЩ features.

   However, it is possible to use both one after the other.


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Org Mode,  Prev: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.5 Compatibility with Whitespace-mode
=======================================

вАШWhitespace-modeвАЩ and вАШuniline-modeвАЩ are mostly compatible.

   Why activate вАШwhitespace-modeвАЩ while in вАШuniline-modeвАЩ?  Because
вАШUnilineвАЩ creates a lot of white-spaces to implement an infinite buffer.
And it is funny to look at this activity.

   To make вАШuniline-modeвАЩ and вАШwhitespace-modeвАЩ fully compatible,
disable the newline visualization:

   вАҐ вАШM-x customize-variable whitespace-styleвАЩ
   вАҐ uncheck вАШ(Mark) NEWLINEsвАЩ

   This is due to a glitch in вАШmove-to-columnвАЩ when a visual property is
attached to newlines.  And вАШuniline-modeвАЩ makes heavy use of
вАШmove-to-columnвАЩ.


