13.6 Compatibility with Org Mode
================================

You may want to customize the shift extension mode in вАШOrg ModeвАЩ.  This
is because вАШOrg ModeвАЩ preempts вАШshift-select-modeвАЩ for other useful
purposes.  Just type:

     M-x customize-variable org-support-shift-select

   and choose "when outside special context", which sets it to вАШtвАЩ.

   You then get the shift-selection from вАШOrg ModeвАЩ, not from вАШUnilineвАЩ.
The difference is that the вАШUnilineвАЩвАЩs one handles the infinite-ness of
the buffer.

   Other than that, вАШUnilineвАЩ is compatible with вАШOrg ModeвАЩ

   Thanks to jdtsmith (GitHub) for sharing a funny fact he discovered.
If a source block is created with the вАШUnilineвАЩ language (вАШUnilineвАЩ is
*not* a language like вАШC++,вАЩ вАШPythonвАЩ, or вАШBashвАЩ), then it can be edited
(вАШM-x org-edit-specialвАЩ) with вАШuniline-modeвАЩ automatically activated.



     #+begin_src uniline
     вХ≠вФАвФАвФАвХЃ   вХ≠вФАвФАвФАвХЃ
     вФВ вХЈ вХ∞вФАвФАвФАвХѓ вХЈ вФВ
     вФВ вХ∞вФА    вХґвФАвХѓ вФВ
     вХ∞вХЃ вЧП     вЧП вХ≠вХѓ
      вФВ      вХЈ  вФВ
      вХ∞вХЃ вФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ вХ≠вХѓ
       вХ∞вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвХѓ
     #+end_src


