14.3 Example: Lisp function to draw a plus sign
===============================================

For instance, if we want to create a function to draw a "plus" sign, we
can code it as follows:

     (defun uniline-draw-plus ()
       (interactive)
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС 1)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС 1)
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС 1))

   Calling вАШM-x uniline-draw-plusвАЩ will result in this nice little
plus-shape:



      вХ≠вХЃ
     вХ≠вХѓвХ∞вХЃ
     вХ∞вХЃвХ≠вХѓ
      вХ∞вХѓ
     generated by
     M-x uniline-draw-plus

   We may modify the function to accept the size of the shape as a
parameter:

     (defun uniline-draw-plus (size)
       (interactive "Nsize? ")
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР size)
       (uniline-write-dwвЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР size)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС size)
       (uniline-write-lfвЖР size)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС size)
       (uniline-write-riвЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-upвЖС size))

   The вАШ(interactive "Nsize? ")вАЩ form prompts user for the size of the
shape if not given as a parameter.

   This API works in any mode, not only in вАШUnilineвАЩ minor mode.  It
takes care of the infiniteness of the buffer in the right and down
directions.


