15.1 use-package, the straightforward way
=========================================

The вАШuse-packageвАЩ library became the de-facto standard to manage
packages in your вАШ.emacsвАЩ initialization file.  The вАШuse-packageвАЩ
library comes along with Emacs.  It can (among other services) delay
loading external packages until they are used, and bind keyboard
shortcuts to the packageвАЩs entry points.

   Add the following lines to your вАШ.emacsвАЩ file, and reload it, if not
already done.  This says that the popular Melpa repository is one of the
central store of third parties packages.  To day, it provides almost
7000 packages to choose from.

     (add-to-list 'package-archives
                  '("melpa" . "http://melpa.org/packages/")
                  t)
     (package-initialize)

   Alternately you may customize this variable:

     M-x customize-variable package-archives

   Then add those lines in your Emacs initialization file (usually
вАШ~/.emacsвАЩ):

     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   or:

     (use-package uniline-transient
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   This tell Emacs:
   вАҐ Be prepared to load вАШuniline-modeвАЩ when the user request it, but do
     not load it now.
   вАҐ Bind the вАШC-<insert>вАЩ keys to the function вАШuniline-modeвАЩ.  This
     shortens the longer вАШM-x uniline-modeвАЩ command.  Any other key
     combinations can be bound, as you prefer.  вАШ<insert>вАЩ happens to
     also be the key used inside вАШUnilineвАЩ (customizable).
   вАҐ Load either the вАШuniline-hydraвАЩ or the вАШuniline-transientвАЩ file, as
     you prefer.  This gives Uniline one or the other flavour of
     user-interface.

   There is an alias to вАШuniline-hydraвАЩ:

     (use-package uniline
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   If you are using *note straight.el:: with вАШuse-packageвАЩ, and have
вАШ(setq straight-use-package-by-default t)вАЩ, you have the following
options:

     ;; uniline-hydra using the alias
     (use-package uniline)

     ;;; uniline-hydra explicitly requested
     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :straight uniline)

     ;;; install and load uniline-transient
     (use-package uniline-transient
       :straight uniline)


